The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Two policemen, including an officer of the wireless department of Calcutta police, were suspended on Monday for allegedly demanding money from a car driver on BT Road, near Rabindra Bharati University, on November 11. The accused had intercepted a car and demanded money from the driver as he was carrying loads of books. A man in the car suddenly opened the rear door to get down when a motorcycle rammed into the door from behind. Pillion rider Nimai Ghosh, 55, was critically injured and died soon after. The cops sped away after the mishap.    Power supply to the Kabir Road, Janak Road, SP Mukherjee Road, Satish Mukherjee Road, Jatin Das Road, Deshapriya Park and Lake Place areas may be disrupted between 9.30am and 11.30am because of maintenance by CESC.    Avijit Dey and Jaydip Joani, who used to run a company from their AB 169 office in Salt Lake, were arrested on Monday following a complaint by employees that they had not been paid for the past month.    Five men were arrested on the Calcutta airport premises early on Monday. Police said the men had assembled to plot a robbery.    The West Bengal Council of Higher Secondary Education said on Monday that the last date of issuing and submission (with late fine) of registration forms for students of Class XI of the 2010-2012 session had been extended till November 22.    Three persons were arrested with a tiger skin in Baruipur on Monday evening.    Pradeep Sharma, who had fled with Rs 15 lakh that his employer had asked him to deposit in a Burrabazar bank a fortnight ago, was arrested at his Teghoria home on Monday.    Bablu Das, 38, died after he fell off a Barasat local while it was approaching Haroa Road station on Monday morning. He was taken to Barasat District Hospital where he was declared dead.    Police arrested Laal Shaw and Tapas Bhattacharya on Monday on the charge of snatching on local trains. The duo were caught by passengers when they tried to snatch a womans chain on a Lakshmikantapur local on Sunday night.    A fire broke out inside an ATM counter of the United Bank of India on the ground floor of 14 Brabourne Road late on Sunday. Four tenders doused the flames in 20 minutes.                                                                                                                                               
